Note that all shocks are unfinanced - see 'The reaction of the public sector'
 in the introduction.
 It should also be noted that all the shocks are partial shocks from the
 point of view of the foreign economy (rest of the world), as foreign demand
 and interest rates are unchanged.
 
\end_layout

